    excerpt: "iPhone-specific tips for getting the most out of ChatGPT, including Siri integration, Shortcuts automation, and iOS-native workflows.",
    content: `<p>ChatGPT on iPhone benefits from deep iOS integration that Android users do not have. From Siri Shortcuts to Focus Mode integration and native share sheet support, there are dozens of iPhone-specific tricks that make ChatGPT more powerful and convenient. Here are twelve tips that every iPhone ChatGPT user should know.</p>

<h2>1. Set Up ChatGPT in the Shortcuts App</h2>
<p>Open the Shortcuts app and create a new shortcut. Add the "Ask ChatGPT" action (available after installing the ChatGPT app). You can pre-fill prompts, set the model, and chain the response into other actions like sending an email, creating a note, or copying to clipboard. Once created, add your shortcut to the Home Screen for one-tap access to any ChatGPT workflow you use regularly.</p>

<h2>2. Use Siri to Launch ChatGPT</h2>
<p>With Shortcuts integration, you can trigger ChatGPT from Siri. Create a Shortcut with a voice-friendly name like "Ask my AI" and Siri will recognise it as a command. You can even pass Siri's voice input directly into a ChatGPT prompt, creating a seamless voice-to-AI pipeline. This works while driving with CarPlay, with AirPods, or any time Siri is accessible.</p>

<h2>3. Use Focus Modes to Manage Notifications</h2>
<p>iOS Focus Modes let you control when ChatGPT can send notifications. In Settings, tap Focus, select or create a mode, and configure allowed apps. For a "Work" focus, allow ChatGPT notifications so you never miss response completions. For a "Personal" focus, silence ChatGPT to avoid work distractions. This granular control ensures ChatGPT is helpful without being intrusive.</p>

<h2>4. Master the Share Sheet</h2>
<p>When you select text anywhere on your iPhone, the share sheet appears. With a ChatGPT Shortcut configured to accept shared text, you can send selected text directly to ChatGPT from any app without manually copying and pasting. Create shortcuts like "Summarise this text" or "Improve this writing" that take the shared input and return the result to your clipboard.</p>

<h2>5. Voice Mode with AirPods</h2>
<p>Advanced Voice Mode works beautifully with AirPods. Open ChatGPT, tap the headphone icon, and start speaking. ChatGPT responds through your AirPods in a natural voice. You can interrupt, ask follow-ups, and have a genuine conversation. The latency is low enough for real-time dialogue. This is ideal for walks, commutes, or any time you want to brainstorm without looking at your screen.</p>

<h2>6. Use the Action Button for Quick Access</h2>
<p>On iPhone 15 Pro and later, configure the Action Button to run a ChatGPT Shortcut. Press once to immediately start a voice conversation with ChatGPT or open a new chat with a pre-set prompt. This is the fastest possible way to access ChatGPT on any phone, reducing the time from idea to prompt to a single button press.</p>

<h2>7. Copy Text Without Formatting Issues</h2>
<p>iPhone users face specific <a ${L} href="/guides/chatgpt-text-cleaner-iphone">text formatting issues</a> when copying from ChatGPT. To get clean text, long-press on a response in the ChatGPT app and use the copy button rather than manually selecting text. Then paste into Notes first as a plain-text intermediary before sending to your final destination. This two-step method removes most hidden formatting artifacts.</p>

<h2>8. Use Dictation in the Input Field</h2>
<p>Besides ChatGPT's built-in voice mode, you can use Apple's native dictation in the text input field. Tap the microphone on the iOS keyboard to dictate your prompt. The advantage over ChatGPT's voice input is that you can see the transcription in real time, edit it, and add to it before sending. Apple's dictation also works offline for basic transcription on newer iPhones.</p>

<h2>9. Widget on Home Screen and Lock Screen</h2>
<p>Add the ChatGPT widget to your Home Screen or Lock Screen for instant access. The widget shows a quick-start button that opens a new conversation immediately. On the Lock Screen, this means you can start talking to ChatGPT without even unlocking your phone fully, saving several seconds per interaction.</p>

<h2>10. Use iCloud Sync Across Devices</h2>
<p>Your ChatGPT conversations sync across all Apple devices signed into the same account. Start a conversation on your iPhone during your commute, then continue it on your iPad or Mac when you arrive. This seamless continuity means you never lose context when switching devices.</p>

<h2>11. StandBy Mode with ChatGPT</h2>
<p>When your iPhone is charging in landscape orientation (StandBy Mode on iPhone 15+), you can interact with ChatGPT widgets and voice commands. This transforms your charging iPhone into an always-ready AI assistant on your desk or nightstand.</p>

<h2>12. Clean Text with a Shortcut</h2>
<p>Build a Shortcuts automation specifically for <a ${L} href="/blog/how-to-copy-chatgpt-text-on-mobile">cleaning ChatGPT text</a>. The shortcut takes clipboard text, runs replace actions to remove asterisks, normalise spacing, and strip em dashes, then puts the clean text back on the clipboard. Add it to the Share Sheet and you can clean any ChatGPT response in one tap from any app. For more formatting solutions, see our <a ${L} href="/guides/clean-chatgpt-text">text cleaning guide</a>.</p>`
