    content: `<p>ChatGPT on iPad offers a significantly different experience from the iPhone version. The larger screen, support for Split View and Stage Manager, Apple Pencil compatibility, and hardware keyboard support transform ChatGPT into a desktop-class productivity tool that you can use anywhere. Here is how to take full advantage of the iPad experience.</p>

<h2>Why iPad Is Great for ChatGPT</h2>
<p>The iPad's larger screen means you can read longer ChatGPT responses without scrolling constantly, which makes it ideal for research, long-form writing assistance, and code review. The ability to run ChatGPT alongside other apps in split view creates workflows that are impossible on a phone: for example, having ChatGPT open next to your note-taking app, writing tool, or web browser simultaneously.</p>

<h2>Split View and Stage Manager with ChatGPT</h2>
<p>To use ChatGPT in Split View, open ChatGPT, then swipe up to see the dock, and drag another app to the side of the screen. ChatGPT resizes fluidly to accommodate the split. This is ideal for workflows where you are researching in Safari and asking ChatGPT questions simultaneously, or where you are drafting content in Pages while using ChatGPT as a writing assistant.</p>
<p>On iPads that support Stage Manager (M1 chip and later), you can have ChatGPT in a floating window alongside multiple other apps. Resize the ChatGPT window to any dimension, overlap it with other windows, and arrange your workspace exactly as you need it. This is the closest experience to using ChatGPT on a desktop computer.</p>

<h2>Using the Apple Pencil with ChatGPT</h2>
<p>While ChatGPT does not have native Apple Pencil drawing input, you can use Scribble to handwrite your prompts in the text input field. Write naturally with the Apple Pencil and iPadOS converts your handwriting to typed text. This is convenient for quick questions when you are already using the Pencil for notes or sketches in another app. You can also take handwritten notes with the Pencil, photograph them, and send the image to ChatGPT for transcription or analysis.</p>

<h2>iPad Keyboard Shortcuts for ChatGPT</h2>
<p>When using a hardware keyboard (Magic Keyboard, Smart Keyboard, or Bluetooth), ChatGPT supports several keyboard shortcuts. Press Return to send a message, Shift+Return for a new line within your prompt, and Command+N for a new conversation. These shortcuts make the ChatGPT iPad experience feel like a native desktop application and significantly speed up your workflow compared to touch-only interaction.</p>
<p>Create text replacement shortcuts in iPad Settings under General, then Keyboard, then Text Replacement. Add frequently used prompt fragments so you can type a short abbreviation and have it expand into a full prompt template. For example, typing "qqblog" could expand to "Write a 500-word blog post about" followed by your cursor position.</p>

<h2>Managing Long ChatGPT Sessions on iPad</h2>
<p>The iPad's larger screen makes it practical to have very long ChatGPT conversations that would be tedious to scroll through on a phone. Use conversation pinning to keep important long-running sessions accessible. When a conversation grows beyond useful length, ask ChatGPT to summarise the key points and decisions, then start a new conversation with the summary as initial context. This keeps response quality high, as very long conversations can sometimes cause ChatGPT to lose track of earlier context.</p>

<h2>Sharing ChatGPT Output from iPad</h2>
<p>The iPad's share sheet is more capable than the iPhone's, offering additional options for many apps. When you copy ChatGPT responses on iPad, you have the same <a ${L} href="/blog/how-to-copy-chatgpt-text-on-mobile">formatting considerations</a> as on iPhone, but the larger screen makes it easier to spot and fix issues before sharing. Use the two-step paste method — paste into Notes or a plain-text editor first, then copy to your final destination — for the cleanest results. For more on keeping your text clean, see our <a ${L} href="/guides/clean-chatgpt-text">text cleaning guide</a>.</p>
<p>The iPad is also excellent for creating content with ChatGPT and then editing it immediately in a professional app like Pages, Notion, or Ulysses, all running side by side. This create-then-clean workflow takes advantage of the iPad's multitasking strengths and is one of the best ways to use <a ${L} href="/blog/chatgpt-mobile-productivity-tips">ChatGPT for mobile productivity</a>.</p>`
